<span id="freeTextContainer8622784384323348922">I stumbled upon Mother in my summer vacations when i was in class 6th. Too young to understand the deep meanings behind the words, i was hooked just to pass my summer holidays. but as i went through the pages, i was able to see that this book is one true tribute to a journey of a woman, a mother. a woman who after taking all the suffering silently looks towards her son for a better life. who is not able to understand why her only son has to join the revolution. who cries with pain, fear of loosi</span>
  <span id="freeText8622784384323348922" style="display:none">I stumbled upon Mother in my summer vacations when i was in class 6th. Too young to understand the deep meanings behind the words, i was hooked just to pass my summer holidays. but as i went through the pages, i was able to see that this book is one true tribute to a journey of a woman, a mother. a woman who after taking all the suffering silently looks towards her son for a better life. who is not able to understand why her only son has to join the revolution. who cries with pain, fear of loosing her son to czar. but when She understands the real meaning of the noble cause, also joins in with her son. how true her soul must have been. she becomes an epitome of courage, strength and truth. ..<br />Mother is an incredible journey of a woman who stands tall despite all odds in her life. <br /><br />this book remain my most beloved book till date and i always recommend this one to read....</span>
