<div id="review_3763283785" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3763283785" />
    <a title="Waleed Hamza" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/98014689-waleed-hamza"><img alt="Waleed Hamza" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591297400p2/98014689.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3763283785?book_show_action=true">Jan 10, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Waleed Hamza" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Waleed Hamza" href="/user/show/98014689-waleed-hamza">Waleed Hamza</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780806508900" href="/book/show/13246.Mother">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3763283785" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9993825028479520202">Mother by Maxim Gorky.<br/><br/><blockquote>&quot;You will not drown the truth in seas of blood&quot;</blockquote><br/>A story set in the canvas of pre-soviet Russia ,the Czarist regime, THE MOTHER speaks of <b>Pelageya Nilovna Vlasova</b>, a working class woman, and the spouse of a wife-beating tipple. Till her husband&apos;s death she lives the life of an illiterate nobody. Her son, Pavel Vlasov, brought up by her, transforms into a young socialist leader and there starts her journey from a woman haunted by her past to an active force in the Russian soci</span>
  <span id="freeText9993825028479520202" style="display:none">Mother by Maxim Gorky.<br /><br /><blockquote>"You will not drown the truth in seas of blood"</blockquote><br />A story set in the canvas of pre-soviet Russia ,the Czarist regime, THE MOTHER speaks of <b>Pelageya Nilovna Vlasova</b>, a working class woman, and the spouse of a wife-beating tipple. Till her husband's death she lives the life of an illiterate nobody. Her son, Pavel Vlasov, brought up by her, transforms into a young socialist leader and there starts her journey from a woman haunted by her past to an active force in the Russian socialist movement.<br /> <br />All the other elements aside, the way Gorky has sketched the character transition of the mother, leaves you awe-stricken. <br />In the face of hardships, oppression and arrestings, for all the young comrades, deprived of family love and affection, she remains a mother, a fountain to pour your heart into.<br />This profound piece of soviet realism is a story of motherly love in the face of an indifferent world, a story of resilience and hope in the face of oppression and cruelty and the story of the downtrodden in the face of autocratic Czarist elite.<br /><br /><b>A slow paced, 4/5 read recommended to those who read realist literature and not to those who are more into fantasy as it can get boring.</b></span>
  <a data-text-id="9993825028479520202" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


