<div id="review_2792315307" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2792315307" />
    <a title="اُمامہ " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/50052704"><img alt="اُمامہ " src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2792315307?book_show_action=true">Aug 01, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="اُمامہ " class="user" itemprop="url" name="اُمامہ " href="/user/show/50052704">اُمامہ </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback " href="/book/show/56397544-mother">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=literature">literature</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/50052704?shelf=russian">russian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2792315307" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12659231928934241361">All my life, I have been ridiculously obsessed with Russia: It’s history, culture and most importantly, its geography. The reign of Czars, the Bourgeoise domination, the proletarian movements, the Soviet Union’s formation and its supremacy, Stalin’s era, and the years of revolutionary crusades. This was my first book on Russian literature, and after immediately reading it after The Communist Manifesto, I immensely and thoroughly enjoyed it, and actually better understood it, through the tale of </span>
  <span id="freeText12659231928934241361" style="display:none">All my life, I have been ridiculously obsessed with Russia: It’s history, culture and most importantly, its geography. The reign of Czars, the Bourgeoise domination, the proletarian movements, the Soviet Union’s formation and its supremacy, Stalin’s era, and the years of revolutionary crusades. This was my first book on Russian literature, and after immediately reading it after The Communist Manifesto, I immensely and thoroughly enjoyed it, and actually better understood it, through the tale of actual characters. <br />This is a story of a mother and her son who after years of monotonous routine of working and bowing to the Czars and higher authorities, describes how the workingmen stood up against the atrocities and injustice. The true protagonist of novel, the mother, who despite being politically ignorant, rose up to the revolution due to her maternal feelings, and portrayed the perfect empowered character. <br />Vladimir Lenin himself described this book as of utmost importance. Highly recommended. 💯</span>
  <a data-text-id="12659231928934241361" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


