        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer53226317" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6238245817995264064"> M.Gorky&apos;s book is the story of a movement in Russia during the second half of the 19th century to the begining of the 20th century.The story of the common people against autocratic czar and the capitalists.It is about a family&apos;s life surviving in a time like this and fighting for revolution.This novel tells the story of a mother supporting her son fight for the rights of the people.<br/> I thought this book was really good and I would&apos;n have read it if my mother hadn&apos;t recommended it to me. It took </span>
  <span id="freeText6238245817995264064" style="display:none"> M.Gorky's book is the story of a movement in Russia during the second half of the 19th century to the begining of the 20th century.The story of the common people against autocratic czar and the capitalists.It is about a family's life surviving in a time like this and fighting for revolution.This novel tells the story of a mother supporting her son fight for the rights of the people.<br /> I thought this book was really good and I would'n have read it if my mother hadn't recommended it to me. It took me a while to read it because it is over 500 pages, but i managed. So in turn i recommend this book to people who enjoy historical fiction or nonfiction books.</span>
