<div id="review_2150952367" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2150952367" />
    <a title="Baykal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72178354-baykal"><img alt="Baykal" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2150952367?book_show_action=true">Oct 14, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Baykal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Baykal" href="/user/show/72178354-baykal">Baykal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/72178354-baykal?shelf=literature">literature</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2150952367" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5625677434395544073">Unless you are a sentimental softy or someone with socialist sympathies (or both), this book is not for you. The plot is dull and lacking twists of any sorts, the characters (aside from the main character- the mother) are not interesting. The narrative offers several long and naive harangues by side characters and this is particularly annoying for readers with some historical and literature background. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

